# Preview and transform

- Transforms are on-demand only — never write derivatives to object storage.
- `transform.Service` takes `engine.Registry`; reads objects via resolved engine.
- Supabase query params: `width`, `height`, `resize`, `format`, `quality` — mapped in `supabase.go`.
- Extended params: `page`, `dpi`, `t` for PDF/Office/video.
- PDF rasterization: HTTP call to preview-worker (`internal/preview/poppler.go`).
- Office: Gotenberg → PDF → Poppler (`gotenberg.go`).
- imgproxy optional via `TRANSFORM_BACKEND=imgproxy` for images only.

Poppler must not be linked into `cmd/server` — sidecar only (GPL).
